@sandstrand I see you're using the interactive merger. Using it I just had the same problem, and I found that the issue was with displaying the image on screen. Processing the whole video without showing it ( `shift`+`>` ) does work for me.  From the stacktrace you provided I see that the Exception occurs in the same location in your case ` cv2.imshow (wnd_name, img)`

To patch it up, I just added a try catch in the location where `cv2.imshow` was called and causing an issue. This worked for me, even if I could not see the problematic frames anymore. Which, for me, is fine for now.

**The (*not quite*) fix:**
FILE: `DeepFaceLab_NVIDIA_RTX3000_series\_internal\DeepFaceLab\core\interact\interact.py` -> line `466`

change this function:
```python
    def on_show_image (self, wnd_name, img):
        cv2.imshow (wnd_name, img)
```

to this:
```python
    def on_show_image (self, wnd_name, img):
        try:
            cv2.imshow (wnd_name, img)
        except Exception:
            pass
```
